    <note>Shi Hao [10642] See documentation for descendants, Jiuling [10644], Shoudao [10663], Kegong [10643], and Yaofu [10648]. According to Wei(5) Liaoweng's [4001] funerary inscription for Yaofu, Hao moved to Danleng when he was Linqiong county magistrate during the reign of Tang Xuanzong (r. 847-859), whereas other sources have him holding the same office, but moving at end of Tang. I will accept the more exact date, not out of line with end of Tang move, but, since county magistrate office may have been at an early period of his civil service career, make the active year 870. This would place the move of Yan [10627], founder of the Qingshen Shi(5) lineage, at approximately the same time.</note>
